1
00:00:06,139 --> 00:00:09,710
(Kim Ye Rim)

2
00:00:12,579 --> 00:00:16,116
(Kang Sang Jun)

3
00:00:19,419 --> 00:00:22,923
(Ko Ju Hee, Jung Hyun Min)

4
00:00:27,828 --> 00:00:32,032
(Azure Spring)

5
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:33,300
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

6
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:34,535
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

7
00:00:34,535 --> 00:00:35,769
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

8
00:00:35,769 --> 00:00:37,004
(for filming child actors and animals.)

9
00:02:11,565 --> 00:02:12,499
Go!

10
00:02:12,499 --> 00:02:13,534
And they're off!

11
00:02:13,534 --> 00:02:16,270
Han Ye Kyung of South Korea
makes a perfectly clean dive.

12
00:02:16,770 --> 00:02:18,071
Now she's breaking the surface.

13
00:02:18,071 --> 00:02:19,773
And she begins her freestyle stroke.

14
00:02:20,507 --> 00:02:22,609
Her strokes are fluid,
and her rhythm is consistent.

15
00:02:22,609 --> 00:02:25,712
She's nearing the halfway mark.

16
00:02:26,613 --> 00:02:28,215
Into the turn!

17
00:02:28,916 --> 00:02:29,883
Looking good!

18
00:02:29,883 --> 00:02:32,019
Perfect touch on the wall,
and a smooth change of direction.

19
00:02:32,019 --> 00:02:34,054
She's picking up the pace with ease.

20
00:02:34,321 --> 00:02:36,990
And now heading into the final ten meters!

21
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,392
Han Ye Kyung.

22
00:02:38,392 --> 00:02:40,627
Han Ye Kyung! Touches!

23
00:02:41,628 --> 00:02:42,529
First place!

24
00:02:42,529 --> 00:02:44,898
It's a gold medal! Gold medal!

25
00:02:45,532 --> 00:02:46,834
What an unbelievable moment!

26
00:02:46,834 --> 00:02:50,170
Gold has returned
to Korean women's swimming.

27
00:02:50,537 --> 00:02:52,873
A rising star and a true dark horse,

28
00:02:52,873 --> 00:02:55,742
Han Ye Kyung finally makes her mark.

29
00:02:55,742 --> 00:02:56,510
Thank you.

30
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:59,146
What a proud moment for Han Ye Kyung!

31
00:02:59,413 --> 00:03:02,516
We are living in the era of Han Ye Kyung.

32
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:04,017
(Han Ye Kyung: New National Record
Women's Swimming, South Korea)

33
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:05,786
Dreams do come true.

34
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:10,257
(Han Ye Kyung: New National Record
Women's Swimming, South Korea)

35
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:12,326
Of course,

36
00:03:13,327 --> 00:03:15,195
it doesn't necessarily
have to be my dream.

37
00:03:41,154 --> 00:03:48,128
(Episode 1
Rise or Fall, We're Still Young)

38
00:04:33,173 --> 00:04:34,775
"Pa" for waves, and "Rang" for beauty.

39
00:04:35,709 --> 00:04:37,678
Parang-ri,
where the ripples are beautiful,

40
00:04:38,045 --> 00:04:39,680
even in the mountainous Namhae region,

41
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,415
is a village famous
for its shimmering ripples.

42
00:04:44,985 --> 00:04:46,620
Beyond the edge of Tongyeong,
you have to take a boat...

43
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:49,523
an hour deeper into the sea
to find this backwater village.

44
00:04:54,795 --> 00:04:55,696
This is...

45
00:04:56,563 --> 00:04:57,664
my hometown.

46
00:05:34,067 --> 00:05:34,968
This is tiring.

47
00:06:12,906 --> 00:06:14,174
It's been five years,

48
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:16,210
and why is it so spotless?

49
00:06:17,644 --> 00:06:19,146
No need for any cleaning.

50
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:16,029
Mom never used the iron pot.

51
00:08:16,964 --> 00:08:18,298
After a long day of diving,

52
00:08:18,298 --> 00:08:20,234
hauling over a hundred pounds of seafood,

53
00:08:20,767 --> 00:08:23,103
coming home to this heavy pot...

54
00:08:23,504 --> 00:08:26,840
to lift it, scrub it,
and even grease it down...

55
00:08:27,474 --> 00:08:28,575
was something she refused to do.

56
00:08:38,418 --> 00:08:39,953
But once a year,

57
00:08:40,254 --> 00:08:41,421
on my birthday...

58
00:08:41,421 --> 00:08:43,891
she'd fill this very pot
with the seaweed she'd caught that day...

59
00:08:43,891 --> 00:08:45,292
and cook me seaweed soup.

60
00:09:07,514 --> 00:09:08,649
This is unusual.

61
00:09:09,216 --> 00:09:10,784
At home, for the first time
in a long while,

62
00:09:11,585 --> 00:09:14,521
of all things, I cook seaweed soup
in this iron pot.

63
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:17,558
Seo Anna.

64
00:09:18,125 --> 00:09:18,992
Happy birthday.

65
00:10:04,938 --> 00:10:06,707
Just living in hiding like this...

66
00:10:07,708 --> 00:10:09,142
might not be that bad.

67
00:10:34,434 --> 00:10:35,435
This is the person!

68
00:10:36,537 --> 00:10:38,138
I told you before, don't you remember?

69
00:10:41,508 --> 00:10:42,809
Good grief.

70
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:44,745
(Parang Harbor Fishermen's Association)

71
00:10:44,745 --> 00:10:45,579
Where is it?

72
00:10:46,346 --> 00:10:47,181
Here!

73
00:10:47,714 --> 00:10:48,582
Take a look.

74
00:10:50,584 --> 00:10:52,419
- Thanks for the effort.
- Thank you.

75
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:55,722
There's a kid looking for a room
in the village.

76
00:10:55,722 --> 00:10:57,491
Is it okay to rent out your mom's house?

77
00:10:58,926 --> 00:11:00,327
Just let the person live there.

78
00:11:00,327 --> 00:11:01,695
Having someone in an empty house...

79
00:11:01,695 --> 00:11:02,896
is good for upkeep and all.

80
00:11:04,665 --> 00:11:06,500
(Just let the person live there.)

81
00:11:08,769 --> 00:11:09,603
See?

82
00:11:10,938 --> 00:11:12,306
Anna, are you going to stay long?

83
00:11:14,441 --> 00:11:15,676
Aren't you going to swim anymore?

84
00:11:15,676 --> 00:11:17,110
Who says I'm not? I'm still swimming!

85
00:11:17,644 --> 00:11:19,313
There's no need to snap.

86
00:11:20,314 --> 00:11:21,982
If you're just visiting
for a little while,

87
00:11:21,982 --> 00:11:24,651
then you could stay together like family.

88
00:11:25,219 --> 00:11:26,653
It's not like we're living
in the dark ages.

89
00:11:26,987 --> 00:11:28,589
You've got plenty of rooms,
so what's the big deal?

90
00:11:28,589 --> 00:11:29,489
Chief.

91
00:11:30,157 --> 00:11:32,092
There's no need to be afraid of him.

92
00:11:33,293 --> 00:11:34,695
That was a frost-bound stare.

93
00:11:35,629 --> 00:11:38,165
Anyway, you young folks...

94
00:11:38,165 --> 00:11:41,034
figure this out.

95
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:41,902
Got it?

96
00:11:42,369 --> 00:11:43,303
Good.

97
00:11:43,737 --> 00:11:44,705
You two look good together.

98
00:11:45,772 --> 00:11:47,841
Something's going to happen for sure.

99
00:11:53,914 --> 00:11:55,115
Now that it's come to this,

100
00:11:56,316 --> 00:11:57,851
let's just make the best of it together.

101
00:11:59,386 --> 00:12:01,788
Tenant in the guest house,
me in the main house.

102
00:12:02,322 --> 00:12:03,991
As long as we don't bother each other.

103
00:12:04,324 --> 00:12:06,226
Even if you hear the phone,
act like you didn't.

104
00:12:06,226 --> 00:12:08,028
Even if you see what I'm eating,
pretend not to see.

105
00:12:08,362 --> 00:12:09,530
Even if we're living under the same roof,

106
00:12:09,530 --> 00:12:10,931
just like living alone, basically.

107
00:12:11,498 --> 00:12:12,599
What do you say, Mr. Tenant?

108
00:12:19,106 --> 00:12:20,307
Well? Nothing to say?

109
00:12:21,108 --> 00:12:23,777
Are you with me on this?

110
00:12:23,777 --> 00:12:24,845
Or are you out?

111
00:12:25,312 --> 00:12:26,547
Will you be staying long?

112
00:12:28,182 --> 00:12:30,184
First the village chief, and now you...

113
00:12:30,184 --> 00:12:32,019
why does everyone keep asking me
how long I'll be here?

114
00:12:32,519 --> 00:12:33,353
Very long...

115
00:12:33,654 --> 00:12:34,888
for a very, very long time.

116
00:12:35,322 --> 00:12:36,223
Forever.

117
00:12:36,557 --> 00:12:37,991
I really hope so.

118
00:12:41,662 --> 00:12:42,863
Did you just blow me off?

119
00:12:44,464 --> 00:12:45,332
Hey.

120
00:12:45,832 --> 00:12:46,700
Hey!

121
00:12:51,305 --> 00:12:52,172
Hey!

122
00:12:53,674 --> 00:12:54,641
Seo Anna!

123
00:12:55,375 --> 00:12:56,510
It's you, right?

124
00:12:57,044 --> 00:12:57,845
Who are you?

125
00:12:59,179 --> 00:13:00,280
It's really you.

126
00:13:00,547 --> 00:13:03,517
The Mermaid of Parang-ri, Seo Anna!

127
00:13:04,718 --> 00:13:06,486
It's been years.

128
00:13:06,486 --> 00:13:07,921
Mermaid, what?

129
00:13:09,523 --> 00:13:11,391
Do you remember me?

130
00:13:13,861 --> 00:13:16,630
The Trot Goddess of Parang-ri.

131
00:13:16,630 --> 00:13:18,265
Baek Su Jeong!

132
00:13:18,866 --> 00:13:22,302
Oh, my goodness
Oh, my goodness, don't do this

133
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:26,807
A woman's heart is like a reed

134
00:13:27,074 --> 00:13:30,644
Don't do this, what's wrong with you?
Don't ask me

135
00:13:31,278 --> 00:13:35,816
You can't want me anymore

136
00:13:36,984 --> 00:13:40,587
Today it's the first time I met you

137
00:13:46,693 --> 00:13:49,129
Who dares to run away
while the Trot Goddess of Parang-ri...

138
00:13:49,129 --> 00:13:50,531
is performing?

139
00:13:50,764 --> 00:13:51,798
Sorry.

140
00:13:52,633 --> 00:13:54,801
I've got swimming practice.

141
00:13:55,736 --> 00:13:57,838
Fair enough, the Little Mermaid
needs her swim training.

142
00:13:58,238 --> 00:13:59,873
Have a great time! Keep it up!

143
00:14:00,374 --> 00:14:01,375
Okay, got it.

144
00:14:03,343 --> 00:14:04,311
Now, focus.
I'll start over.

145
00:14:06,079 --> 00:14:09,650
Oh, my goodness
Oh, my goodness, don't do this

146
00:14:13,587 --> 00:14:14,688
I'm doomed.

147
00:14:17,257 --> 00:14:18,859
So much for living on my own.

148
00:14:19,626 --> 00:14:22,196
Truly, a singer's voice
is their fingerprint.

149
00:14:22,496 --> 00:14:24,865
I guess you remembered me
as soon as you heard the song?

150
00:14:26,066 --> 00:14:26,934
I knew it.

151
00:14:27,734 --> 00:14:29,603
And so much for living a quiet life.

152
00:14:30,070 --> 00:14:31,004
And so,

153
00:14:31,305 --> 00:14:33,040
I heard you went to Seoul
to be a competitive swimmer.

154
00:14:33,307 --> 00:14:34,541
Why are you back out of the blue?

155
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:38,412
Well...

156
00:14:38,912 --> 00:14:40,681
The Parang-ri Mermaid,
who was said to be a swimmer in Seoul,

157
00:14:41,014 --> 00:14:42,683
is actually...

158
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:54,328
My goodness...

159
00:14:54,695 --> 00:14:56,597
you look tired these days.

160
00:14:57,097 --> 00:14:59,533
Your boyfriend must be quite strong?

161
00:15:01,368 --> 00:15:02,269
What?

162
00:15:02,269 --> 00:15:04,771
I said, your boyfriend
must be quite strong.

163
00:15:04,771 --> 00:15:05,672
Tidy up here.

164
00:15:09,843 --> 00:15:11,411
Little Mermaid? Yeah, right.

165
00:15:13,547 --> 00:15:16,717
I'm no longer the Parang-ri Mermaid.

166
00:15:22,422 --> 00:15:24,124
Hey, stop. Stay still.

167
00:15:24,124 --> 00:15:24,992
Don't move.

168
00:15:25,359 --> 00:15:26,560
Hey, don't move.

169
00:15:27,361 --> 00:15:28,896
Today, your...

170
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:32,299
your booty is in top shape.

171
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:36,003
One little brush against this,

172
00:15:36,370 --> 00:15:37,905
it feels like it's about to snap.

173
00:15:38,972 --> 00:15:39,873
Hey!

174
00:15:42,843 --> 00:15:45,012
Hey. Did you just say "hey" to me?

175
00:15:45,279 --> 00:15:46,146
You heard me. I said "hey."

176
00:15:46,146 --> 00:15:47,915
What! You creep!

177
00:15:47,915 --> 00:15:50,184
- I'm going to kill you!
- Watch your language with me.

178
00:15:50,884 --> 00:15:53,387
You're lucky I'm letting this slide today.

179
00:15:54,154 --> 00:15:56,089
- You are so dead.
- Wait.

180
00:15:57,291 --> 00:15:58,458
Hey, my nose is bleeding.

181
00:16:00,294 --> 00:16:01,628
Hey, Seo Anna.

182
00:16:02,095 --> 00:16:04,298
Don't bother coming in from tomorrow!

183
00:16:06,266 --> 00:16:07,835
You're fired!

184
00:16:26,086 --> 00:16:27,821
It's been a while
since I've actually swum.

185
00:16:28,889 --> 00:16:30,757
I just worked a part-time job at a pool,
but I lost it.

186
00:16:34,228 --> 00:16:36,697
There's no need to
tell this to Parang-ri's...

187
00:16:37,297 --> 00:16:38,899
chatterbox, Baek Su Jeong.

188
00:16:40,334 --> 00:16:41,335
Why are you back?

189
00:16:42,669 --> 00:16:45,205
I mean, why are you here?

190
00:16:45,973 --> 00:16:46,840
Just.

191
00:16:48,108 --> 00:16:49,176
It's just so unfair.

192
00:16:49,176 --> 00:16:50,010
Unfair?

193
00:16:50,777 --> 00:16:51,612
What is?

194
00:16:52,913 --> 00:16:53,881
By the way,

195
00:16:54,448 --> 00:16:56,483
about the guy who lives in my house.

196
00:16:57,150 --> 00:16:58,418
Are you talking about Deok Hyun?

197
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,587
He's older?

198
00:17:01,421 --> 00:17:02,456
Anyway.

199
00:17:02,456 --> 00:17:04,558
What's his deal?

200
00:17:06,226 --> 00:17:07,327
A male sea diver.

201
00:17:07,594 --> 00:17:08,996
- A male diver?
- Yes.

202
00:17:09,296 --> 00:17:10,697
He dives for a living.

203
00:17:10,964 --> 00:17:11,965
And he looks...

204
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:15,035
incredibly cool doing it.

205
00:17:28,115 --> 00:17:30,317
Deok Hyun, nice!

206
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:36,557
Though the area is a bit uphill,

207
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:38,759
you'll be okay after a few trips.

208
00:17:39,793 --> 00:17:40,861
Nice.

209
00:17:40,861 --> 00:17:42,029
Ain't it nice?

210
00:17:44,631 --> 00:17:45,465
This place...

211
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:48,735
has an incredible view.

212
00:17:49,770 --> 00:17:51,104
His name is Yun Deok Hyun.

213
00:17:51,338 --> 00:17:53,006
Age, occupation, and past...

214
00:17:53,941 --> 00:17:55,075
unknown.

215
00:17:55,075 --> 00:17:57,711
Out of nowhere one day...

216
00:17:58,979 --> 00:18:01,882
Drifted in like the wind

217
00:18:01,882 --> 00:18:03,784
A mysterious young man

218
00:18:05,686 --> 00:18:06,520
Wait.

219
00:18:07,287 --> 00:18:08,255
No way...

220
00:18:09,389 --> 00:18:11,058
are you interested in Deok Hyun too?

221
00:18:11,525 --> 00:18:12,426
Too?

222
00:18:15,395 --> 00:18:17,764
Don't tell me you're interested in him.

223
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,001
You tell me first.

224
00:18:21,268 --> 00:18:22,903
Weren't you only staying for a short bit?

225
00:18:22,903 --> 00:18:24,304
Aren't you going to swim?

226
00:18:24,304 --> 00:18:26,240
I am. I'm going to.

227
00:18:26,406 --> 00:18:27,908
Why are you being like this too?

228
00:18:28,609 --> 00:18:30,777
Plus, I'm not interested in him at all.

229
00:18:32,212 --> 00:18:33,747
What's there to like about such a jerk?

230
00:18:34,448 --> 00:18:36,283
A jerk?

231
00:18:37,050 --> 00:18:39,486
A young male diver shrouded in mystery.

232
00:18:40,521 --> 00:18:42,356
Isn't that too sexy?

233
00:18:44,558 --> 00:18:45,526
Sexy?

234
00:19:11,351 --> 00:19:13,353
What part of him is even remotely sexy?

235
00:19:13,353 --> 00:19:14,788
He's just dark and tanned, that's all.

236
00:19:18,725 --> 00:19:20,194
Oh, you got a baby sea bream there?

237
00:19:20,194 --> 00:19:21,795
That'll be so tasty in a soup.

238
00:19:21,995 --> 00:19:23,197
Didn't we agree...

239
00:19:23,197 --> 00:19:25,365
to just look the other way
regarding what we eat?

240
00:19:28,535 --> 00:19:30,704
I'm just saying, that's all.

241
00:19:31,805 --> 00:19:34,274
Like I said, baby sea bream
is really good in soup.

242
00:19:35,209 --> 00:19:36,143
Information!

243
00:19:46,019 --> 00:19:47,120
Sexy? Sure.

244
00:19:47,921 --> 00:19:49,356
He's a snotty scumbag.

245
00:19:51,525 --> 00:19:53,060
What the...

246
00:20:18,051 --> 00:20:19,553
This middle-of-nowhere village.

247
00:20:20,254 --> 00:20:22,122
Eating is the only joy.

248
00:20:25,559 --> 00:20:26,593
Wake up, Seo Anna.

249
00:20:27,361 --> 00:20:28,929
Like he'd actually give it to me
if I asked.

250
00:20:29,229 --> 00:20:30,497
Have you no pride?

251
00:21:07,034 --> 00:21:08,735
(Snack Bar
Sea Squirt & Pork Belly Available)

252
00:21:08,735 --> 00:21:10,370
(Ramyeon, Gimbap, Noodles)

253
00:21:14,775 --> 00:21:16,376
What kind of snack bar closes at seven?

254
00:21:29,857 --> 00:21:30,958
Why aren't you answering my calls?

255
00:21:31,291 --> 00:21:32,626
Don't tell me you blocked me?

256
00:21:33,694 --> 00:21:36,196
Are you unaware of how tight
the owner is with the association?

257
00:21:37,431 --> 00:21:39,399
Are you going to quit swimming for good?

258
00:21:39,399 --> 00:21:40,234
(Ignore xxx)

259
00:21:50,077 --> 00:21:51,578
Where did all that sparkle go?

260
00:21:52,946 --> 00:21:54,281
It's just pitch black now.

261
00:21:55,549 --> 00:21:58,418
It's so dark,
even a ghost could hide.

262
00:22:21,074 --> 00:22:22,009
I'm hungry.

263
00:22:42,930 --> 00:22:43,997
Mr. Tenant!

264
00:22:45,933 --> 00:22:46,867
Anybody there?

265
00:22:51,705 --> 00:22:52,573
Is he gone?

266
00:22:54,308 --> 00:22:55,609
Excuse me.

267
00:23:01,014 --> 00:23:02,115
You out?

268
00:23:10,324 --> 00:23:11,692
Wow, so organized.

269
00:23:12,526 --> 00:23:13,794
Typical. This says everything about him.

270
00:23:21,602 --> 00:23:23,403
Where did he hide it?

271
00:23:34,214 --> 00:23:36,917
Never lose that food radar, Seo Anna.

272
00:23:48,161 --> 00:23:49,096
Sea squirts?

273
00:23:49,863 --> 00:23:51,498
Why did he freeze these beauties?

274
00:23:51,932 --> 00:23:53,834
Should've mixed in a bowl of rice
right then and there.

275
00:23:56,203 --> 00:23:57,371
Well, I guess I'll have to
eat them myself.

276
00:24:00,174 --> 00:24:02,776
(Parang-ri)

277
00:24:02,776 --> 00:24:04,578
Chief, I'd like to use the field a bit.

278
00:24:04,578 --> 00:24:05,812
Do as you please.

279
00:25:01,602 --> 00:25:03,270
Nothing soothes you in the morning...

280
00:25:03,270 --> 00:25:05,973
like a bowl of clear fish soup.

281
00:25:08,909 --> 00:25:11,845
If you make that clear fish soup
with pufferfish, it's pufferfish soup.

282
00:25:12,246 --> 00:25:14,515
And if you use a baby sea bream,
like me right now...

283
00:25:14,915 --> 00:25:16,350
then it becomes baby sea bream soup.

284
00:25:50,484 --> 00:25:53,387
The classic way for sea squirt
is mixing it on the spot with rice,

285
00:25:53,387 --> 00:25:55,589
lettuce, and a dash of sesame oil.

286
00:25:56,890 --> 00:25:58,525
Still, sea squirts
that missed their timing...

287
00:25:59,092 --> 00:26:01,728
can be a real treat
when made into pancakes.

288
00:26:18,846 --> 00:26:21,148
When ingredients are iffy,

289
00:26:21,148 --> 00:26:22,449
Rule one of solo living...

290
00:26:26,253 --> 00:26:27,221
oil is the answer.

291
00:27:35,522 --> 00:27:36,423
I should...

292
00:27:37,858 --> 00:27:38,926
go back, right?

293
00:27:49,136 --> 00:27:51,371
Does sharing the kitchen
include sharing the food too?

294
00:27:52,372 --> 00:27:53,307
Gosh, you scared me.

295
00:27:57,444 --> 00:27:58,378
Well, you see...

296
00:27:58,912 --> 00:28:00,147
I thought you'd thrown them away.

297
00:28:01,181 --> 00:28:03,483
Then, they'd be in the trash,

298
00:28:03,483 --> 00:28:04,551
not the freezer.

299
00:28:06,787 --> 00:28:09,690
It's just fish scraps and sea squirt.
Don't be so cheap about it.

300
00:28:10,123 --> 00:28:11,792
Do you think catching sea squirts is easy?

301
00:28:12,793 --> 00:28:14,528
Don't act so special
just because you dive.

302
00:28:15,629 --> 00:28:17,965
I was quite a swimmer myself, you know.

303
00:28:18,232 --> 00:28:19,733
You're using the past tense,

304
00:28:19,733 --> 00:28:21,034
so I guess you no longer...

305
00:28:23,437 --> 00:28:24,271
swim.

306
00:28:25,906 --> 00:28:27,341
- What?
- Or...

307
00:28:28,108 --> 00:28:29,109
you can't.

308
00:28:30,844 --> 00:28:32,713
Hey, what do you know about me?

309
00:28:32,713 --> 00:28:34,948
Whatever it is, it'll be best
to make up your mind soon.

310
00:28:35,249 --> 00:28:36,149
About what?

311
00:28:37,518 --> 00:28:39,686
Whether you're going to commit
and settle down here.

312
00:28:39,686 --> 00:28:41,054
Or if you're just here for a breather...

313
00:28:41,054 --> 00:28:42,389
before going back to your old life.

314
00:28:43,524 --> 00:28:45,792
People who wallow in self-pity,

315
00:28:45,792 --> 00:28:47,561
ruin this village's mood,
and then just leave.

316
00:28:47,995 --> 00:28:49,062
I've seen it all too many times.

317
00:28:52,299 --> 00:28:53,200
Information.

318
00:29:03,610 --> 00:29:04,578
Seo Anna!

319
00:29:08,248 --> 00:29:09,616
Why'd you quit your part-time job?

320
00:29:10,050 --> 00:29:11,952
Don't you know who the boss is?

321
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:14,688
How could I not know.

322
00:29:15,355 --> 00:29:17,291
Yes, I was obsessed because
I never got Mom that gold medal,

323
00:29:17,291 --> 00:29:19,092
and so I trained
day and night without rest.

324
00:29:19,092 --> 00:29:21,195
So you pulled strings to get this job...

325
00:29:21,562 --> 00:29:23,764
for your "washed-up" girlfriend.

326
00:29:24,331 --> 00:29:26,099
You said he's close
with the association president...

327
00:29:26,099 --> 00:29:28,235
and that he could help my comeback
even after a few years off.

328
00:29:28,235 --> 00:29:29,303
You know exactly!

329
00:29:30,337 --> 00:29:31,738
But you screw up like that?

330
00:29:33,507 --> 00:29:35,275
Do you really want to ruin your life?

331
00:29:36,476 --> 00:29:37,978
How can everyone so easily judge...

332
00:29:39,413 --> 00:29:41,782
whether someone's life is ruined or not?

333
00:29:43,684 --> 00:29:45,452
As your swim coach for nine years.

334
00:29:46,253 --> 00:29:47,855
As your boyfriend for three years.

335
00:29:49,389 --> 00:29:51,758
Anna, I've known you for 12 years.

336
00:29:52,993 --> 00:29:53,827
Right?

337
00:29:55,762 --> 00:29:57,197
Are you done with swimming?

338
00:29:57,998 --> 00:30:00,968
Do you want your name
to stay as Seo Anna, the failed prospect?

339
00:30:10,744 --> 00:30:11,645
Seo Anna.

340
00:30:12,813 --> 00:30:13,914
This is my last warning.

341
00:30:15,215 --> 00:30:16,183
Put down the suitcase.

342
00:30:18,352 --> 00:30:19,453
Jerks.

343
00:30:20,287 --> 00:30:21,255
You're going to pay for this.

344
00:30:27,361 --> 00:30:28,495
Where did he go?

345
00:31:26,353 --> 00:31:27,621
Since when was there a sea like this...

346
00:31:29,489 --> 00:31:30,824
hidden behind Parang-ri?

347
00:31:37,264 --> 00:31:38,031
What?

348
00:31:38,432 --> 00:31:39,199
What's that!

349
00:32:40,527 --> 00:32:41,929
Rise or fall, we're still young.

350
00:32:43,197 --> 00:32:45,599
Thank you.

351
00:32:45,866 --> 00:32:47,067
Silence.

352
00:32:47,601 --> 00:32:48,569
Enough eating.
Everyone focus.

353
00:32:50,003 --> 00:32:51,705
Our Korea National Sport University.

354
00:32:52,506 --> 00:32:53,473
Our ace,

355
00:32:54,141 --> 00:32:55,475
Ye Kyung will give a toast.

356
00:32:56,977 --> 00:32:58,178
Our ace.

357
00:32:58,579 --> 00:33:02,482
Ace!

358
00:33:03,116 --> 00:33:04,117
I'll go with...

359
00:33:05,319 --> 00:33:07,321
"Rise or fall, we're still young!"

360
00:33:07,955 --> 00:33:09,122
Rise or fall!

361
00:33:09,122 --> 00:33:11,391
We're still young!

362
00:33:13,827 --> 00:33:15,462
- Bottoms up.
- Okay.

363
00:33:16,096 --> 00:33:17,030
Eat up.

364
00:33:17,030 --> 00:33:18,532
Even this isn't enough.

365
00:33:27,274 --> 00:33:30,310
They say, "Rise or fall,
we're still young."

366
00:33:34,915 --> 00:33:38,218
But the youth I knew wasn't like that.

367
00:33:54,668 --> 00:33:55,903
Success is youth,

368
00:34:00,307 --> 00:34:03,510
but failure is just pathetic.

369
00:34:14,755 --> 00:34:17,891
That's why I hate being called a failure.

370
00:34:18,959 --> 00:34:20,394
I fought just as hard as anyone else.

371
00:34:21,695 --> 00:34:22,596
No,

372
00:34:23,063 --> 00:34:24,765
maybe I fought even harder than they did.

373
00:34:44,284 --> 00:34:45,185
What is it?

374
00:34:45,953 --> 00:34:47,020
How did you find this place?

375
00:34:53,293 --> 00:34:54,494
Teach me how to dive too.

376
00:34:58,432 --> 00:34:59,299
What?

377
00:34:59,766 --> 00:35:01,702
Let's just say the fish heads were trash,

378
00:35:02,169 --> 00:35:04,238
but I'll make up for the sea squirts.
I'll dive for them.

379
00:35:06,740 --> 00:35:08,208
It was just a passing remark.

380
00:35:08,575 --> 00:35:09,443
Forget about it.

381
00:35:11,111 --> 00:35:11,979
Hey!

382
00:35:15,782 --> 00:35:18,685
Who blabs about someone's life
being ruined as a passing remark?

383
00:35:19,720 --> 00:35:20,854
I'm a good swimmer.

384
00:35:21,388 --> 00:35:24,057
I was even a national youth athlete.

385
00:35:24,992 --> 00:35:27,060
If you show me how,

386
00:35:28,495 --> 00:35:29,930
I'll get those sea squirts for you.

387
00:35:31,765 --> 00:35:32,866
So,

388
00:35:34,535 --> 00:35:35,802
teach me how...

389
00:35:36,837 --> 00:35:37,804
to dive.

390
00:35:41,975 --> 00:35:43,143
My life isn't ruined.

391
00:35:45,012 --> 00:35:46,246
Parang-ri Mermaid...

392
00:35:46,780 --> 00:35:48,081
isn't washed up yet.

393
00:35:58,959 --> 00:35:59,826
(Mi Hyun's daughter)

394
00:35:59,826 --> 00:36:01,295
Just let the person live there.

395
00:36:03,030 --> 00:36:04,131
She says just live here.

396
00:36:05,999 --> 00:36:06,867
Okay.

397
00:36:07,267 --> 00:36:08,669
But I'll still pay the rent.

398
00:36:10,504 --> 00:36:12,206
Make yourself at home.

399
00:36:13,607 --> 00:36:16,543
You can use a room in the main house
or the guest house.

400
00:36:37,764 --> 00:36:39,399
She looks like a real handful.
